A quick look through at what it’s like being at Disney World’s 50th anniversary! 🐭🫶🏻 Time is ticking and the event is only through March 31, 2023! If you haven’t been yet - make sure you go for this once in a life time chance for celebration! I had so much fun and it was really worth my trip.

⚠️ Tips for your Disney World Trip ⚠️

🎟️ When buying tickets, I found the most convenient and best deals via @themeparkfrog - they had rates that were better than my family’s discount through corporate.

🗓️ Admission into theme parks are required to be booked online in advance. This means that the parks are not all available every single day. Even after buying tickets, you must look at their official webpage to view their calendar and park availability. I was not able to go to Hollywood Studios due to the dates not being available anymore. So I recommend buying tickets in advance and booking dates way in advance as well!

🧞‍♂️ To make better use of time, spend a little more on Genie+ Pass (sometimes there will be a bundle where you purchase with admission which makes it cheaper. Or you can decide to buy by day. Maybe you don’t need it for every theme park. But I find it the best deal to buy with admission after I tried NOT buying it with admission and regretted it.) It starts at $25 per person and it’s like their flash pass where you can reserve a time slot for a ride. I found it worth it as you can do more with your time and be more leisure rather than rushing and wasting your time lining up you can sight see! Genie+ pass is limited availability everyday so get it early and ASAP.

🪔 If you have Genie+ pass you can book as soon as you arrive to the park so book the more popular rides first and time it accordingly. I would typically book something and then wait in a short line for a less popular attraction. Then go to my reservation and then make my next and so on so forth.

📸 It’s extra, but if you want to cherish your memories - pay for PhotoPass! Unlimited photos throughout the park & Disney Springs to document your vacation! Plus fun exclusive filters! It is $169 if you buy it in advance and $199 if you buy it upon arrival!

#disneyworld50 #disneyworldorlando

Am I right? Or am I right? 😜

Disney is definitely pricey. 💸 And I’ll be first to admit, it does break the bank. There’s always controversy on the price whenever I scroll Reddit, FB, online forums or just talk to people. But to me - the experience you get there, the energy from the people just having fun there and the kindness of the staff beats it all. At the end of the day, it is still “the happiest place on earth.” ✨🐭 And yes, I am happy there! 🤩

Yes. I’m telling you that you can have someone document your entire Disney vacation for just one price. 📸 Which I found totally worth it. Because well, usually hiring a photographer will cost you at the bare minimum $100 an hour. (I’ve traveled and hired photographers everywhere around the globe. And yes it’s expensive. 😳 But you’re paying for someone’s professionalism!) And, yeah you can ask someone to take a pic on your phone, but professional equipment has its perks and you won’t have to bother someone else on vacation! 🤗

Disney’s Memory Maker for Photo Pass is $169 if you buy in advance or $199 if you decide to buy it there. And it covers 30 days of photos at Disney Photopass locations, which will cover your entire trip and at any of the parks & Disney Springs. There are so many locations for photo spots. If you visit all the Disney parks you can get photos for all of them in just one package! 😉 Would you get Memory Maker if you were to go to Disney?

Sharing a carousel of some of my pics from Disney PhotoPass Memory Maker 🐭✨📸 Many more where this came from, but these are just a selected few that I had downloaded onto my phone. 🤭(a bit lazy to sort through all the other files to be honest cause we took so many haha!)

Went to Disney right before pandemic and right after. 😳Cause it’s my happy place haha.

PS: Disney PhotoPass Memory Maker is priced at $169 for advanced purchase, $199 when you buy it there!

⚠️ TIPS for MEMORY MAKER ⚠️

- Buy it in advance to save $30!

- Each family/couple/group only needs one pass to share PhotoPass. So you can easily split the cost. Just keep in mind since there is only one pass holder account, the group will have to stay together for photos when the pass is being scanned so the photos can be transferred to that account. However, you can take photos in whatever group you form when the photographer takes the photos!

- If you are not going to all Disney parks or spending less days there and only want photography from a certain park (a lot of people only want Magic Kingdom). I would suggest doing the $69 day pass. And it will cover one day of photography!

- When buying Memory Maker in advance, you need to buy it 3 or more days prior to the date you go in order to have it activated for that price.

- You can view and download photos in real time! So those real time social media posts are a YES! 🤩

Tried this for you guys first cause of all the hype I saw around it.✌🏻Reporting back with my experience! Their dine in is a small area downstairs and they have a gallery of their cakes and pastry upstairs with a take-out section.

Their signature “Corn” is usually always sold out. That’s why when booking - I booked their signature menu so that they will reserve a piece for me. However, when you go to your booking and change your mind - you don’t have to commit to that signature menu if you end up wanting less. It is $58.90 for 3 cakes and a pastry. For your first time though, I would highly suggest booking the signature menu if you want to try a variety of things. The price for it is same as if you ordered a la carte. It includes: The Corn, Apple-Yuja Tart, Lysée and Kouign Amann.

⭐️ The “Corn” 7.5/10 for it’s unique corn flavor. I think typically I would give it a 7. But I haven’t had a cake quite like this one with the corn flavor & props to the creativity in it. It’s creamy and rich. A bit overbearing to my palate to be honest. But it tastes like those Korean corn puff snacks if you catch my drift.

⭐️ Apple-Yuja Tart 8.5/10 possibly my favorite. It’s delicate and refreshes my palate. With all 4 on the table - I reached for this the most. Probably because the others were creamier and richer in taste. If I had this “alone” maybe my rating would change.

⭐️ Lysée 8/10 is very nutty in flavor and bold. The nuttiness was almost gritty. Some may like it. Some may not. It is a clear contrast to the Corn which was very creamy. I liked it more at first. Then the excitement died down. But I can see the embodiment of the Korean flavors in this one. Plus it’s super pretty!

⭐️ Kouign Amann 8/10 I had this first because I knew it would be less sweet than the others. I wanted to taste the flavors before my palate got used to sweetness. Rich and buttery goodness. But have I had better? Yes. Would I get it again here? Yes. 🤷🏻‍♀️

One of those cliche “follow me” photos with my ring. 💍😂Cause literally had friends asking for it lol. For my Q&A a lot of you asked about the ring actually! So here’s me answering a few of those questions here!

💬Did he pick the ring out himself?
💁🏻‍♀️It was collaborative. We went ring shopping together within our first or second year of dating as we already knew this day would come sooner or later. 🫶🏻So he had a good idea of what I liked. Of course tastes change over a decade so he did take me again last year to take a look. I ultimately chose 3 designs I liked and he chose the final one! Ultimately it ended up being at the same jewelers and brand we chose 10 years ago and the design was similar too. Proves we like the same thing for a long time!

💬What brand is your ring?
💁🏻‍♀️It is a @tacoriofficial ring chosen by him. We both grew up watching FRIENDS and this was the brand of the ring Chandler proposed to Monica with in their apartment. And featured in one of our favorite episodes of when Chandler went ring shopping with Phoebe. So he always had a soft spot for them. Ultimately he chose this one for the intricate details.

💬Where is your ring from?
💁🏻‍♀️We wanted to shop from a local jeweler that can service/clean our ring bi-annually. And have attention to detail. So he went with @hlgrossjewelers we went to them when we first started dating and came back 10 years down the road. 😂True loyalty.

💬Are you going to wear the ring when you continue your travels?
💁🏻‍♀️Short answer. Yes. But it really depends where I am going. So it will depend on situation and I will be making logical choices. I’m a klutz, but I have yet to lose any of my fine jewelry pieces. Thank God! But just in case, he did buy jewelry insurance from @brite.co so that I could just wear it stress free. We don’t see the point of locking up and safe guarding something you’re supposed to wear! After all - it’s “price per wear” 🤪

📍 El Retiro Rose Garden, Madrid Spain

Happy Mid-Autumn Festival! 🥮🌕🐇🎑 Mooncakes are a once a year thing just for this special holiday where families gather and celebrate together. The fullness of the moon represents “fullness and unity”. With the crops abundant, our stomachs are full, and family can be together happily. Mooncakes represent that same concept with added sweetness! 😋 It’s an unbreakable tradition to have Mooncake during the holiday…

But it honestly has gotten so fancy with all the variations of Mooncakes on the market. We bought 3-4 variations to share with family this year. But this @ladymcakes one gotta be the most unique! 🫶🏻Their limited edition box set doubles as a jewelry box! 🤭And is shaped as a moon arch for good luck and IS PINK! 💕 

They have a lot more limited editions releasing! Will you be keeping an eye out?

PS: in full honestly, two posts in a row featuring them but not sponsored 🤣just a coincidence. I just got this box set delivered yesterday and thought it was too beautiful not to share. ✌🏻
